I would like to request a feature enhancement.   When I attempt to associate a workflow scheme with a project by selecting the "Associate" link next to the workflow name, it displays a box with all the projects to which I can apply the selection.  The problem is that it also shows projects ALREADY associated with said scheme in highlighted fashion.  If I am not careful, I may simply click the project I want to associate and inadvertently deselect projects already associated.  This may happen, for example, if the projects already associated with the scheme are out of view (requiring to use the scroll bar to bring them into view).  If this mistake is made, the projects will be de-associated from the scheme and set to the default scheme.  This has happened several times at my company already.

A solution I propose is to show only the projects which are NOT associated with the scheme.  This will prevent projects from being de-associated by mistake.

Thanks

